3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the approximation factor for the 2-edge-connected spanning multigraph problem, which is a key concept in game theory. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with fundamental classes of extreme points and their properties, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of finding the integrality gap for the LP relaxation of the 2-edge-connected spanning multigraph problem, which is a topic in computational complexity theory.
